name: Ben Adams
review_text:
We had a wonderful stay at Falls Creek Alpine Resort. The chalet was warm, comfortable, and perfectly suited for a cozy alpine getaway. Everything was well maintained, with thoughtful touches that made it feel welcoming after a day on the slopes.

The location is fantastic--easy access to the lifts and village, with beautiful mountain views all around. Staff were friendly and helpful, making the whole experience smooth and enjoyable.

Highly recommend Falls Creek Alpine Resort for anyone looking for a relaxing, picturesque escape in the snow. We'll definitely be back!

review_text: Great resort for family winter holidays but some things can be improved like the poor positioning of EV chargers without any protection from blizzard conditions. The Gully car park was closed due to the heavy snowfall and preventing access to EV charging stations. Playing music in the common area in front of Slalom Plaza ski lift makes it gloomy compared to other Alpine resorts. DJ music in front of ski lift flat area will warm up the atmosphere in the late afternoons. The Last Hoot restaurant block is an eye sore for the whole ski resort experience and should be removed for opening up to fabulous views of the mountain and Halleys Comet ski run.

name: Ghada El Zohbi
review_text:
After arriving in Bright on 20 June 2025, I suffered a fractured ankle before using any part of my Falls Creek Beginner Bundle. I was hospitalised and referred for surgery in Melbourne. I immediately informed Falls Creek, providing medical certificates and hospital documents, explaining I couldn't ski this season or next.

Falls Creek offered only a voucher, which is unusable given my long recovery. Despite multiple follow-ups with full medical evidence, they have since ignored me.

By contrast, the ski gear hire company we booked with showed compassion and refunded us in full, despite similar policies.

Falls Creek's lack of response has added stress during an already difficult time. I hope they improve their customer care and treat situations like this more compassionately.

name: Mia Roncoroni
review_text: We went skiing here at the end of July this year. Unfortunately, we were quite disappointed considering the very high price. There was a day of heavy rain, and for half the day they only kept a small slope open with just one ski lift operating. We asked if it was possible to get a refund or a voucher for another day, but it was completely denied. We also found the chairlifts really outdated and slow; they definitely need to be improved or at least made rainproof... for $220 you can not provide such outdated chairlifts! The slopes were poorly maintained and skiing was unpleasant due to numerous small bumps, holes, and snow piles. Additionally, the slopes were poorly marked, making it easy to get lost in low visibility. Lastly, the city slopes were ruined by the constant passage of snowmobiles! Even the restaurants on the slopes, managed by completely unmotivated staff, left us disappointed. If you don't have a phone with internet connection, you can't view the menu or place an order, and often the Wi-Fi didn't work.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Mia, we are sorry to hear you were disappointed with your visit to Falls Creek this winter. 
We will pass on your feedback to Falls Creek Ski Lift Company (Vail Resorts) as they manage the ski runs, grooming, ski lifts, lift tickets and the refund policy as a part of their terms and conditions of purchase. You may also send them the feedback directly via https://www.skifalls.com.au/contact-us.  
They do their best to ensure the safety of guests on the slopes and lift operations may vary due to the weather conditions. 
Thank you, Alpine Resorts Victoria - Falls Creek

name: Mike Lyle
review_text:
What a strange place is Falls Creek. After 36 years of skiing all over the world, this was my first time courtesy of the Epic pass. Definitely the snobbiest of the Victorian "Resorts". It has obviously been developed to be self serving for the elite who are members of the private lodges there. Unless you are prepared to pay for a formal sit down meal at a restaurant in the village, the lack of public areas is shocking. Well we did find the official designated "public area" (and signed as such) - a couple of dirty couches in a corner outside the toilets. Every door we opened we were confronted with a "Please Wait to be Seated" sign. Found Hoots was OK if you're happy to have a pizza and watch the beginners come down Wombats Ramble. The skiing was pretty good once you get up the top, and Cloud 9 is a decent place to have lunch or a snack (only $19 for a bowl of sweet potato chips) but no Picnics allowed (also signed in multiple languages on every pole). Thanks for dropping the entry fee by $20 before the end of August due to the absence of operating lifts, but we already got the message, and as outsiders do not feel welcome here and not likely to return 
Check out Hotham instead, we found it to be much friendlier and convenient with welcoming cafes and bars close together in the Village. And you can get the village lift there right back to the carpark!
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Mike, we are sorry to hear that you did not enjoy our experience at Falls Creek Resort and felt unwelcome by other guests. 

There is a large variety of accommodation from club lodges, self-contained apartments, hotels, lodges that welcome the public to stay as well as a large full time community.

Within the Slalom Plaza area there are 3 designated day shelters available to the public, it sounds like you found the one in St Falls Resort. If you were inclined to visit again, please ask any Falls Creek staff member where the other 2 day shelters are located. 

Cloud 9 is a restaurant run by a private operator and this is why there is signage asking guests not to bring their own food. 

Falls Creek Village is 1km from Windy Corner to the Village Bowl, all within walking distance so you can access the 32 restaurants, cafes and bars throughout the village. 

Here at Falls Creek, you do not need to get a lift to the carpark as you can ski down Wombat's Ramble to Slalom Plaza with carparking directly across the road. When conditions permit you can do the same to the Gully Carpark. 

If you did wish to visit again, please come and see the team at the Visitor Information Centre and they can provide you with all these insights and more to give you a better experience here at Falls Creek. 

Thank you again for your feedback.

name: Luke Matias
review_text:
This is a very difficult review to leave, as our family are regular visitor to Falls and LOVE the resort. But the Resort Management have recently (a couple of weeks before school holidays!) put a total ban on venues using their transport vehicles (Cam Ams) to move to and from lifts/restaurants etc.

This has made our trip far more difficult (4 children in our party) through no fault of our magnificent venue (Astra Lodge) who will now, along with many others unfortunately have their businesses impacted by decisions outside of their control.

The aim is obviously to gauge revenues from the small businesses on the mountain and is entirely disgusting. Another case of many SME's being bullied by large corporate mismanagement.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Luke, we appreciate your concern for the business operators that are offering this service but unfortunately, it does sounds like you have not received the full details the situation. There has been no direct ban put in place just before the school holidays. 

There are many legalities and licenses that must be obeyed under Victorian Law and the Victoria Road Rules. Alpine Resorts Victoria have an obligation to ensure that those operating oversnow vehicles on the resort roads are meeting these regulations. 

Limiting the use of oversnow vehicles around the village improves the public amenity, pedestrian safety and overall operations within the resort. For safe transport about the mountain, 4Site is the company that operate shuttles around the village and directly to your accommodation when arriving and departing the resort. They also offer a taxi service during the hours that the free shuttles are not operational

Please contact info.fallscreek@alpineresorts.vic.gov.au if you wish to discuss your concerns further. 

Kind regards, 
Alpine Resorts Victoria - Falls Creek

review_text:
Visited and skied recently. Downhill slopes were in good condition and enjoyable. Cross country was good too.

One star due to resort plans to extend resort area and carparks over existing cross country trails, which will ruin this unique area and destroy the sensitive alpine environment.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Peter. We are disappointed to hear that you a giving the resort a 1-star review for a project that is currently going through stakeholder and community consultation.

If you have not done so already we recommend you visit corporate.fallscreek.com.au/lakeside-development-project-planning/.  Here you can view details regarding project planning, stakeholder engagement, and detailed FAQs.

You can subscribe to receive the consultation survey and receive updates on how the project is progressing. It will also assist in mitigating any misinformation that is currently circulating in the XC community.

The car park at the Observation Deck is currently a designated car park for resort visitors for 8 months of the year outside of the snow season. The proposed clearing of 1.2km of the existing road (out of 65kms of XC trail network) is to provide better accessibility to all visitors to Falls Creek Resort.

Kind Regards, Falls Creek Resort Management

Definitely the longest ride from Melbourne to come here but worth the time. The half an hour up the mountain is windy but lucky for us the weekend ride was good. No snow chains required. But a must to have time if you are going up.
Pick up gear a day before if possible to just hit the slopes rather than spend time with the day trippers queuing to get gear.
Its worth an least a 3 days snow shredding for driving up the windy mountain.
Service to get gear was good. All the lift staff were super friendly. Just book lessons way early if you could. Else prepare to ask on the day and pay 20-30% more.
Cafes and small eateries everywhere. So a hot coffee or beer is always available. Just be warned that Cloud9 is super crowded. School holidays probably as parents brought all the children up for a day trip?
response_from_owner_text:
We wish that a travel portal had been invented to get visitors to Falls Creek quicker but am glad to hear that you felt the 4.5-5 hour drive from Melbourne was worth it.

It is definitely beneficial to collect your rental items such as chains, skis and boots the day before so you can get on the slopes quicker.
Falls Creek Ski Lift company does recommend booking your lessons from them as far in advance as you can along with your lift tickets to secure the best price (a little like an airline).

It is a busy time of the season with the school holidays on at the moment. There are over 35 cafes and restaurants in Falls Creek to enjoy during your visit. We hope you got to stop at a few of them!

Kind Regards, Falls Creek Resort Management.

response_from_owner_text:
Hi Liana, thank you for your feedback.

While googles and helmets are highly recommended a Falls Creek they are not mandatory for use of the ski lifts.  Due to the sales of lift tickets moving to a purely online offer it is more difficult for their staff to make this recommendation but they do have a good webpage on helmets here: https://www.skifalls.com.au/discover-falls-creek/plan-your-trip/essential-information/helmet-policy along with a great checklist of what to bring (https://www.skifalls.com.au/discover-falls-creek/plan-your-trip/essential-information/snow-trip-checklist).

Falls Creek Ski Lifts are a different entity from ourselves but we will pass this feedback onto their customer service team for consideration.

We hope you enjoyed your trip to Falls Creek and hope to see you back again.

Kind Regards,
Falls Creek Resort Management

review_text:
You website is not very intuitive, I had to get the chains separately from my gear because I wanted to collect from two different places.  I booked private ski lessons for the kids, but it's not clear that the private lessons can be for kids too on the website.  We weren't sure as well whether the parents need ski passes if we are only taking the kids to lessons.  The ordering system is not intuitive: I booked group lessons first then booked ski lift passes and it added the $5 card twice and I didn't realize. Also the need for permit to get into the ski resort is not very clear, I only realised that when I stumble across another website about falls creek =_=

I tried to call to ask questions about the above and there is this one day (wednesday) where I called about 20-30 times and no one answered.  No one responded to my emails either and by the time I got through the next day, the preferred lesson time I wanted was fully booked.

However once I DID managed to get through, the customer service was extremely helpful (although ski school didn't know anything abt ski lifts rules for parents taking kids up for lessons) and got most my issues sorted.

The ski instructors are also amazing for the kids and they were skiing in no time.  So it's a bit of a hit and miss in all honesty, but it's mostly good rather than bad.

Shame on you
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Paul. It is very unfortunate that the Falls Creek ski lift company (Vail Resorts) made the difficult to suspend the lift immediately and we understand your frustration.

Falls Creek Resort is not shut. The resort is still open for visitors. Guests were able to continue their holiday within the resort and those not restricted by Stage 3 lock down directives or border closures are still able to visit and stay within the resort.

The ski lifts are not operating but there are other activities that can be experienced at Falls Creek that do continue to support the local businesses.

Thank you,
Falls Creek Resort Management

review_text: We loved Elk, the staff were very accommodating, Jake was awesome, communication was spot on. The transfer in the tracked 4 door Can-Am made it very easy to check in and out. Being able to ski from the front door to the ski lift and then from the top back down to the front door was great. Drying room for gear was fantastic. |The atmosphere and service in the cocktail bar made it a great place to relax at the end of the day. We'll be back.

name: miriamdM801PV
review_text: Very nice, clean and simple room. Super nice to have the restaurant just upstairs for an easy meal. Awesome to get pickup and drop-off service to ATS, Jake was super nice and easy to co-ordinate a time for both trips. Would stay again.

name: robinaK5073DS
review_text: My son and I had a wonderful stay at the Elk. Comfy and modern rooms with a well designed ski room and in room drying cupboard. The Elk offered us private oversnow transfer and a fantastic bar in Apartment 3. Jake and the team looked after us extremely well. I would thoroughly recommend the Elk at Falls for couples and family planning a trip to the snow.

name: Emily_lou89
review_text: We recently stayed at Elk at Falls Creek as a family of four and honestly, it was one of the best ski trips we've had. I actually sat on this review for a while because I kind of wanted to gate keep this place... but they deserve the shoutout.||The location is unbeatable! Elk is conveniently ski-in/ski-out, super close to the Cloud 9 lift (the main lift at Falls Creek and the meeting point for all ski schools and lessons). It's also a stone's throw from ski hire, the most popular restaurants, and the on-slope grocery store. When booking, I had considered other accommodation higher up the mountain and I'm so glad I didn't go that route.||We stayed in Apartment 4, one of the smaller two-bed configurations, it was incredibly well designed, well-equipped, and spotless. Our apartment had a fully equipped kitchen and drying cupboard, which was an absolute lifesaver for soggy ski gear. There's also a communal drying room downstairs  which is fitted out thoughtfully with plenty of storage for boots, boards and skis, a washing machine and plenty of benches to gear up before you walk directly outside onto the snow.||The Elk over snow transfers were a dream at the end of our commute from Melbourne airport. No waiting for Falls Creek paid service or dragging bags through snow or up stairs. Jake, who looked after our transfers and us during our stay was amazing. Friendly, on it, and always happy to help (even helped me to carry skis in each day when the kids had tapped out).||We ate at Sorella most days and managed to extensively test the menu. A must visit, conveniently located inside Elk, the food, wine list and coffee was amazing, the staff beyond friendly and attentive, and the best part? The kids could head back to the room while we finished our wine in peace. ||We were in the apartment directly under Apartment 3, Elks cocktail bar/lounge. We were a little nervous about noise but had no issues at all, No noise transfer. A few reviews raised issue with the noise from the pub down the hill. Whilst we could hear some background buzz it was nothing that interfered with us sleeping when we sank into the comfy beds after a busy day soaking up everything Falls Creek had to offer. ||Add in the magnesium hot tubs to soak tired legs, thoughtful touches , friendly service and the best snow access you could ask for it's no wonder we are already planning next year's trip.||Highly recommend for families, couples, or anyone who wants a comfy, convenient, and well-run base right on the snow.

name: SzuH3
review_text: The owner Jack and the staffs at bar and restaurant are super friendly. The room are super clean and very cozy. Highly recommend this accommodation if you travel to Fallscreek.|Definitely will return for next season.

name: nickoD4949UE
review_text: We stayed 3 days over the weekend at ELK and it exceeded our expectations. The room was super clean, bed was very comfortable and the amenities were fantastic. Cant fault the place and the team were exceptional and looked after us really well.

name: Fearless705753
review_text: We recently stayed at Hotel Elk in Falls Creek for a two-night family ski trip, and it proved to be the ideal base for our winter holiday. Traveling with our five-year-old child, we prioritized comfort, convenience, and family-friendly amenities--criteria that Hotel Elk met with excellence. We are lucky to be the first family visiting Elk this winter season.||From the moment we arrived, the hotel manager, Jake, served as our primary point of contact. He was exceptionally welcoming, attentive, and considerate. He treated all guests, including our young child, with the utmost respect. Understanding that children are naturally curious, he kindly allowed our son to sit beside him at the front of the oversnow vehicle, providing him with a wonderful view of the surrounding scenery.||Jake also provided a thorough orientation regarding the hotel's facilities and the transportation process. His generosity extended further when he offered us a complimentary late check-out on our day of departure. This gesture was tremendously helpful, as we had ski lessons scheduled that morning. The late check-out allowed us to maintain our normal routine, enjoy breakfast, attend lessons, and fully utilize our day on the slopes without the added stress of an early departure. It also allowed us time to rest and prepare for the long 5.5-hour drive home. Such flexibility is not commonly extended by most accommodations, and we deeply appreciated it. Jake's exceptional hospitality and outstanding customer service truly enhanced our stay--even our five-year-old continues to speak fondly of him.||The location of Hotel Elk is second to none. With genuine ski-in/ski-out access, we were able to access the slopes directly from the hotel, greatly simplifying logistics with a young child. It is also within walking (or skiing) distance of ski lifts, equipment rental shops, and several dining options, which proved highly convenient.||The beddings are clean, the pillows are fluffy and comfortable.||Our apartment was warm, modern, and immaculately clean, providing ample space for our family to relax after a full day of skiing.||We dined at the in-house restaurant, Sorella, on the evening of our arrival and found it to be both cozy and inviting. The staff were attentive and accommodating, particularly towards children. The menu offered a well-curated selection suitable for both adults and younger guests.||Additional facilities such as the drying room and ski storage were particularly useful for keeping our gear well-maintained. The area also included laundry amenities (a washing machine and dryer), which were user-friendly and invaluable for washing damp clothing and accessories.||The hotel's three mineral spas were a delightful feature--clean, powerful, and well-maintained. We are especially grateful to the staff who took the time to clear away accumulated snow and ice, ensuring the spas were ready for use on our first night. The water temperature was ideal, offering much-needed relaxation after a long journey.||If any improvements could be suggested, we noted that the dryer in the drying room required cleaning, as the lint filter had accumulated a significant amount of residue. We addressed this ourselves before use. Additionally, the bathroom could benefit from more storage space for toiletries--perhaps an added side trolley would be useful.||In conclusion, Hotel Elk was an outstanding choice for our family ski holiday. It delivered a perfect blend of comfort, practicality, and thoughtful service. We would not hesitate to return and highly recommend it to other families seeking a premium snow holiday experience.

name: Compass54180522481
review_text: Amazing place for family to stay, we arrived late at night, Jake picked up us and helped with all the stuff we brought in, nice room and friendly staffs . My kids loved the hot tub, I loved the dry room which I can get warm boots in the morning, you can ski in/out , will recommend to my friends.

name: Christian Atienza
review_text: Amazing rooms, was warm and cozy as I arrived. Very friendly staff.

name: G1963WYtonyl
review_text: Great room and facility, clean modern and fits well into the mountain surrounding.|Staff Georgie was amazing, helped us with lots of information, including walks and restaurants |Had a fantastic weekend |Would highly recommended staying at Elk at Falls

name: Japs Juinio (vlsvsh)
review_text: Great location. We weren't able to try the warm magnesium tubs. I would like to come back and try next time.

name: Nick Edgerton
review_text:
Well done ELK on making our stay last weekend so great. We travel a lot and its fair to say that Jake and his team communicate better than any place I've stayed.
The bar and restaurant are lovely with great food and the best coffee on the mountain. The room was neat and tidy and completely suitable for a few days at the snow. The drying rooms are a nice touch and a five minute walk to the Halley's Comet lift made for a great weekend.

We will definitely return to the Elk again for our next Falls Creek Holiday

name: Natanael Ryo Kristanto
review_text:
Upon arrival we have been having trouble with the hotel manager Jake. Waited for a very long time at the accomodation transfer centre Falls Creek when we have notified well in advance for our arrival, just for him to show up rudely saying that he's ready to pick us up when we are and not taking care of our gears when we load it up all together to the buggy transport. Our snowboard and ski bag fell of the cart/tray of the buggy and we had to chase after it for him to notice it. Helmet was banged up, board and bindings were damaged. We have our beloved gear that are well taken care of and not a seasoned skiers or boarders with rentals (hence the DB journey bag, if you know you know)
Upon checking in, room wasn't ready, there were cleaners rushing here and there and we have been given the worst room to stay right across the staircase from above (room being in the basement floor). Moldy, small in space for even a family of 3-4. Booking was made months well in advance, paid more than normal rates and surely we'll expect better than this. It's a very discouraging start for our long awaited holiday and definitely a rip off.

name: Young Zou
review_text: We had pre-booked the stay with Elk six months ago and got locked into $3600 for three nights. Based on its uphill location and flourishing photos/marketing materials, we thought that'd be justifiable. However Jake the hotel manager came across very indifferent and rude from the start of the journey. We kept him aware of our arrival at ATS, after waiting 30 mins more we called him again and asked where he was, he negligently said I can be on the way if you are ready.. the baggage's were misplaced in the cart, and first thing that fell out as we were driving uphill was our boards.. The rest of interactions with him were very poor and the apartment's placed in the basement, tiny and mouldy.. There are whole lots of other options up there with similar rates, Elk unfortunately is a poor example of how hotel should run. We would like to warn those looking to book to think again.

name: Matty Wells
review_text:
Pro's
Spa, location, private transfer,

Con's
.No breakfast included (only a tiny breakfast menu available for extra purchase) Basically you have to go out for breakfast.
.No communal/games/fire/lounge areas (you are secluded to your tiny room on bad weather days .
.No sound insulation between rooms, you can hear noise beside and above.
.Dirty sheets
.Rooms don't get serviced, not even over 7 days

Conclusion

You pay a lot for very little, lonely, soulless. I will commend Sorella for nice dinners ( however, extra $$$ of course!!!)

name: Shanti Whitten
review_text: The Elk was a beautiful place to stay and we were treated wonderfully by Leanne who helped us with a last minute room. Such great, comfortable rooms and cosy vibes! Thanks so much

name: Pink Scrunchie
review_text:
Nestled in Falls Creek, a gem so sweet,
A hotel where memories and good times meet.
Jake, the legend, checked us in with grace,
Ignition festival vibes, a smile on his face.

Perfectly placed, just a stroll from the Pub,
In the heart of the action, a prime little hub.
Spas with magnesium, a cyclist's delight,
Easing the body after a day taking flight.

Above and beyond, Jake's service so grand,
A weekend so epic, in this mountainous land.
We'll be back for sure, can't wait to roam,
See you soon, Jake, our Falls Creek home!

name: Erwin Khoo
review_text: Excellent accommodation choice at Falls Creek. Jake and the team at Elk were friendly, welcoming and organised and made our stay a smooth and pleasurable one. The included transfer service took the hassle out of getting from the Transfer Terminal to the accommodation with our luggage. Definitely will be back when are next at Falls!

name: Ella Harris
review_text: Such a beautiful accommodation I stayed here for 3 day with my family it's really close to everything. The bars and restaurants down stairs are so good and the cocktails are amazing and the staff are so friendly

name: wind wind
review_text: The room is very cozy, and supplies three big hot spa tub for relaxing after you ski. Hotel is near the main chair lift. Jake is really nice and hospitality.

name: Christopher Mulcahy
review_text: Elk is piece of European paradise just a hop, skip and jump from Melbourne.  Do yourself a favour and forget about Buller.  Elk is incredible.

name: Adrian Reviews
review_text:
We stayed in September which is off peak so the breakfast was limited to toasted sandwiches (bacon and egg, ham and cheese or vegetable). These were not good. It would be so easy just to serve bacon, eggs and toast instead but they refused.
The biggest problem however was the stupid phone app that you need to use to access the rooms. It is a hassle to set up and it is a total pain when you come in from the snow to get your phone out and take you glove or your goggles and beanie off just to activate the phone so you can get in. It also means you and the kids have to carry their phones everywhere or they can't get into their room. They apparently have wrist bands but didn't have any available. I won't stay here again purely because of this.
On the positive side Jake, the cocktail bar and the restaurant were superb.

name: Sally J (Girlnextdoor24)
review_text: I've been travelling to Falls Creek for many years now and have stayed in many of the available apartments and lodges. Having found Elk, i feel the search for our home away from home at Falls Creek is finally over. The Apartments at Elk are modern, clean and comfortable. Facilities are excellent. The staff are friendly but unobtrusive. The location is perfect. Bob Sugar, the restaurant located on the ground floor is great for breakfast, lunch or dinner followed by a trip to the cosy bar. To cap it all off, Owner Leanne has been great to show us around and introduce us to Elk and Manager Jake - well you could not get a better host. We stayed a couple of times during '22 season and can't wait to return in '23.

name: AN HUANG
review_text: The experience was just amazing! Great location ski in ski out, and Jake is so kind!

name: C h l o e
review_text: Restaurant service was terrible, overpriced and was notified about added %15 surcharge at the end of the service when it was apparently "everywhere", would not come back

name: Luke R
review_text: I highly recommend the beautiful apartments and all the facilities of Elk. Leanne and staff (particularly Jake) are so accommodating and nothing is a problem. Wonderful views, absolutely prime location, ski-in-ski-out, and a great breakfast, too!

name: Harry Bormeisters
review_text: Great location ski in ski out. Helpful service carrying bags on the snowmobile. Very good to have drying cupboards for all your wet snow gear to dry overnight.

name: J
review_text:
Stayed in their suites.

Thought we found our fav hotel at Falls. So many things to love about the place but there are a few major flaws that make me think twice whether I want to stay here again.

Pros
- Jake is so well organised and does not drop the ball. A smooth pick up and drop off!
- No horrendous stairs to climb up at ski in time. Only down.
- Complimentary breakfast (although inconsistent)
- A section of the closet has a heater in it for your ski gear.
- Storage to keep your luggage after check out.
- Outdoor spa is amazing in the 

Cons
- Pillows are nothing pillows and covers were dirty. Comfort = 0, Support=0
- If you want to sleep before 11pm, good luck. Can hear the floor above creaking as people walking non stop. So loud!! Also the doof doof music every night. Not sure if it's from The Man next door or from above, either way it's not enjoyable when you want to rest.
- Breakfast inconsistently cooked each day.
- Complimentary breakfast not so complimentary. Weren't made clear how it works. We weren't charged for extra's on first day but second day we were told it'll cost us. Doesn't make sense to order a simple scrambled eggs with a few extras because you will be charged $5 per extra. Just order the Big Breakfast instead and leave the things you don't want on the plate.

name: Emma Elmer
review_text: Wonderful cocktail bar

name: Jessica Anderson
review_text:
Whole experience from start to finish was amazing. Leanne really helped us last year when we had to reschedule. I was super grateful that they managed the pandemic situation really well. They also emailed me with updates regularly and even gave a detailed list of what we need to organise at the slopes and what they offer, ext. The service we got from Jake was incredible, especially since he was by himself (Two staff away due to covid) This guy was flat chat the whole time we were there, but never ever skipped a beat, he touched base during our 4 days. His organisation was just incredible. We were really impressed. He also did all of this with incredible customer service, he was really genuine and nice. I very highly recommend staying here if you plan a trip to Falls Creek. The hotel room was super comfy, they had chrome cast, heated wardrobe for clothes and it was warm. They have the spa, a bar lounge and Bob Sugar Restaurant, everything you need in one spot. And only a short walk from the chair lift. Cannot thank everyone enough for making out stay super comfortable and enjoyable. Cant wait to come back.

I didn't have many photos from the hotel, but photos on their website are what to expect. here is a beautiful bird that was outside our window and a gorgeous photo they had in the hotel room.

name: Doug Wright
review_text: Had a lovely dinner with fantastic food  , will be back as it's always been a welcoming dinning venue

name: Geoff Woodcock
review_text: Didn't stay here only had dinners and drinks,didn't let me down at all

name: Zheng Fang
review_text: Hua Xue De Zhu Su Jiu Dian,Wei Zhi Hen Hao,Ye Zao Jiu Liao Ji Qi Xia Zhai De Fang Jian.
review_translated_text: The ski accommodation hotel has a great location, but also has extremely cramped rooms.

name: Adem Ibrahim
review_text: Prawn dumplings were 10/10!

name: Brendan Shingles
review_text: One star for accommodation, one for location, one for Jake who looked after us, one for restaurant/bar in the same building, one star for being earthquake proof!

name: Luke Morgan
review_text:
We had the chance to stay in both the twin room and the sub-penthouse during our stay. Both were great value with impressive amenity and a lush modern fitout. The views from the sub-penthouse were stunning!

Location was perfect, just a few hundred metres (downhill!!) and you're at the bottom of Hailey's Comet ready to jet off. It seemed that every restaurant we tried was only a couple minutes walk away also, which was super handy.

Inside there is the bar and restaurant, both of which are top class and delivered amazing food and drinks time after time. No need to leave once you've had a big day out.

Jake was great - accomodating and very helpful. Booking process was practical and simple.

The 40deg spa after big days on the mountain really topped it off. Now a must-do in the recovery routine.

Would recommend to all and hope to be returning for another stay ASAP.

name: Sari King
review_text: Love love love elk

name: Alex Lau
review_text: Excellent location, quality accomodation, and most importantly - EXCEPTIONAL customer service. The free transform from ATS is certainly a game changer. We have been skiing at Falls for years and Elk was the best stay we've ever had. Will definitely come back.

name: Mary Damianos
review_text: Rude staff during lockdown/quarrantine. Reluctant to provide alternate dates and threatened cancellation fee even when I proposed new dates. They think they're the only ones experiencing pain during this tough time, and they are taking it out on their customers who have been trying to support them since the very first lock down in 2020. I could have had a refund, but instead deferred to this year to help support the business. Will NEVER book here again. Good luck Elk! You're acting like wild dogs!!

name: Amy McNamara
review_text: Unfortunately, I didn't get the opportunity to stay at Elk this year due to Covid and border closures in QLD. However, I wanted to give a massive shout-out to the team and thank them for their support, quick responses, and realistic covid booking/cancellation policy.  It is such a difficult time for everyone in the tourism industry and we look forward to supporting and rebooking our trip for next year.  For now, we must play in our own state.  Hopefully see you next year Elk xx

name: Jeffrey Tang
review_text: It's definitely the best place to stay in Falls Creek. We arrived just before the government announced state wide lockdown, but Leanne was really friendly and helpful at pickup even there were quite a lot to take as a business in this hard time. The communication from Richelle from the time of booking to the end of the trip was really clear. Jake was being absolutely great at drop off in our last day. Even though the lifts were closed and the restaurant was closed during our stay, but the luxury and comfortable accommodation, the heavy snow fall for 3 days plus the wonderful foods from Bob Sugars are definitely made our trip even more memorable than a regular winter ski holiday!!! I would highly recommend Elk for anyone planning a trip to Falls Creek and we can't wait for our next stay with Elk!!!

name: Kyle Howard
review_text: Dark inside. Had to use phone flash light to see the menu, food is great

name: Matt Saunders
review_text: Absolutely the best place to stay at Falls! Perfect location, fantastic amenities including loads of storage, spa for aching muscles and newly renovated apartments. Leanne and the team are awesome and the restaurant and bar downstairs perfect with a cozy fire for apres ski. So close to everything that you can come and go as you please. Will be back!!

name: Tony Croke
review_text: Great service from Leanne and the team, awesome restaurant (thanks Bob Sugar team!) and bar, really convenient location in the village. We're looking forward to coming back.

name: samantha glatz
review_text: We recently had the pleasure and privilege of attending the Elk alpine retreat. With the stunning backdrop of Falls Creek, our group enjoyed expertly guided hiking adventures, E-bike tours, Pilates sessions and invigorating yoga classes. The days were interspersed with nourishing, healthy and hearty meals. The accommodation at Elk and the bar are both delightful and welcoming, and the extremely talented duo of Leanne and Jake are to be highly commended for their fabulous hospitality. I could not recommend Elk at Falls highly enough!

name: Juanita Bridger
review_text: Just returned from an amazing Alpine Retreat with Elk at Falls.  It was the perfect balance of mindfulness with yoga and pilates, hiking and e-bike tours through the beautiful countryside and delicious cocktails and food.  Heaven!

name: Mike Redman
review_text: One of my favourite locations in Falls Creek Victoria. Stunning

name: Brett De Vigny
review_text: Gotta love the snow

name: Neil Bates
review_text: Very concerned that forced cancelations due to COVID-19 travel bans are subject to a $300 cancellation fee plus transaction charges. Not good enough.

name: Abby Cheng
review_text: Poor sound insulation rude staff and extra charge fee

name: leigh P
review_text: Very good food, patient with the five children we had in our group and a good selection of wines.

name: Melbourne Tourist Information
review_text: If looking for accommodation or a great place to eat or socialise with friends highly recommend. In the heart of the action ideal winter or summer.

name: Michael Hope
review_text: Beer was expensive otherwise good

name: luke sun
review_text: Mei Ci Lai Xue Shan Du Hui Lai Zhe Jia Dian,Yi Liu De Fu Wu He Shi Wu
review_translated_text: Every time I come to the Snow Mountain, I will come to this store, first-class service and food

name: Gunta Bradley
review_text: We had the steak and it was tender and cooked perfectly. Great steak but could have more veggies. The lamb shank was generous and fell off the bone. The desserts were delicious. The chocolate dessert was a hit and I had the rhubarb freddo which was amazing

name: Li Xiao Dong
review_text: Zhong Zu Qi Shi Fang Jian Hen Zang Fu Wu Tai Du Hen Chai La Di Dui Zheng Ge Xue Cun De Yin Xiang
review_translated_text: Racial discrimination, dirty rooms, and poor service attitude lowered the impression of the entire snow village.

name: James Marshall
review_text: Fantastic food in the restaurant and some great cocktails in the cocktail bar!

name: J B
review_text: Fantastic place to stay, in a great place easy to get to chairlifts. Restaurant is awesome!!

name: Jacob Brady-Walker
review_text:
A.M.A.Z.I.N.G food!
We were there for Father's Day, they were great with the kids, also had plenty of marshmallows for roasting over the roaring open fire.
We make sure we have a meal here every time we go to Falls Creek

name: Mathew de Groen
review_text: Have stayed at Elk for a number of years now for a weekend during the ski season. Rooms are great and Unit 2 has just had a complete renovation and looks great. The pick up service in their own oversnow transport is a great benefit. Easy ski in ski out location. Breakfasts are good generous serves at good pricing. The only letdown is the restaurant at dinner which is overpriced and food average. Otherwise a great place to stay.

name: Edward Geller
review_text:
I am a falls creek regular for the snow season. This was the first time I tried the elk after seeing it many times and regularly having dinner there. Unfortunately the accomodation is poor. The room we had, apartment 10 seems good when you first arrive, the layout and features are fresh and modern. However functionality not so much. We had a large bed, mind you two singles pushed together with a sheet over it; plonked in the centre of the room, good luck trying to walk around the side of it. The room was dirty and not clean at all. The toilet had "residue" on it, the floor felt gritty and not clean. These things are disappointing when you are paying a premium to stay at a place like the elk how ever these can be omitted from your stay due to the fit out and Qulity. The topper for me to mark the elk 1 star was the noise... why ohh why would you put a room directly under the kitchen when the floor is timber.... 530am the banging begins with staff and guests stomping around for breakfast.... and then dinner... that concludes at 11pm

Will I stay at elk again. Never, will I eat at the elk again, most likely not knowing the torture I am putting the people staying at apartment 10 under.

name: Luci
review_text:
Very overpriced, terrible service and food did not match menu. We booked for a table for three and were put on a table for two, we had to place our wine bottle, water bottle and glasses on the floor to make room for the plates. Very noisy venue and one dimensional dishes
Did not feel welcome and would not come back

name: KS Lim (Ks lim)
review_text: Overrated.

name: Catherine Brown
review_text: Awesome breakfast and lovely vibe to Elk. Always a favorite

name: jeff p
review_text: Best restaurant in falls. Great GF options

name: daenan postlethwaite
review_text: Absolutely beautiful place and people at ELK. We stayed over a long weekend and could not have picked a better place! Bazza knows his way around the kitchen too

name: Luwi Kysiakani
review_text: Elk was great. We had lunch here twice during our 2-night snow trip and the food was consistently delicious. They had $22.50 daily specials which were great value for money, and the staff was very lovely. 10/10 would recommend and I will definitely be back the next time I'm at Falls Creek.

name: Evan Johnson
review_text: Wonderful accommodation. The heated floors are divine!! Highly recommended. Makes the holiday so much more relaxing and enjoyable.

name: Vanessa Williams
review_text: Food was fantastic

name: Charles Wheeler
review_text:
Stayed at Elk over the weekend in the newly built penthouse apartment and my mates were on the level below.
Top notch spot. The manger was very friendly, approachable and helpful with any of our needs.
The views from the balcony were sublime especially whilst having breakfast from the table.
All the necessities were included and all appliances worked well.
The only down side is that the bed rooms are short of space for clothing and luggage. It's a bit of a tight squeeze around the bed units.
Would book again for a nice weekend away with a group of people.

name: Dunc R
review_text: Very nice, with great staff. Unfortunately rooms are beneath the restaurant, so constant noise from above

name: Salvatore Di Pietro
review_text: Excellent in every respect

name: Gerry Wunsch
review_text: Awesome, quick service by Rhiannon, amazing food & great ambience. Wld highly recommend. Great suggestion from the best ski instructor Peter Steiner at Falls creek.

name: maria stricek
review_text: The meals are amazing. The staff are great, friendly and efficient. Barry Iddles is an excellent  host.

name: Rob Thomas
review_text: Great place for lunch.

name: Jake Donald
review_text:
Food and service great.
Large portions.

name: Matthew Sykes
review_text: The ambiance of the restaurant was lovely and the staff were very helpful. The food was nice, though not the best. However, we arrived at 7 and were asked to leave at 8:10 given someone else had booked our table. We felt this was a bit sudden, and weren't quite ready to leave. We'd have been alright with this if we'd been told at the start of the meal but an hour to order, eat and enjoy a meal seems quite short.

name: Lauren Hammond
review_text: Great service, the food was incredible. Easily the best salmon I've ever had, and it's reasonably priced as well. I'll definitely go back when I can.

name: Alexander Mavor-Rauschl
review_text: Get the breakfast toastie

name: Cameron Black
review_text: $14 brekky and early bird dinner are great value

name: Natalie Collett
review_text: Fantastic food with generous portions. The beautiful interior design and fireplace was perfect when coming off the ski slopes.

name: Annem Chaudhry
review_text:
Had dinner at the restaurant which was great and vegan friendly (apart from desserts). Staff were eager to help out with the ordering process and happy to recommend items on the menu.
Unfortunately less could be said of the reception staff (Leanne was her name) who made some very classist remarks on the phone today. We considered booking at Elk for accommodation and saw some package deals they had on for September. As a few friends were joining us, we obviously had to consider a budget. The receptionist made some curt remarks of how they're the "second most expensive lodge on the mountain" and if we wanted something cheaper we could "look everywhere else but here".
Thanks for that- we're well aware of the expenses of skiing and how its out of reach for a lot of people who can't afford to go. We have been lucky to stay at QT (which is more expensive) twice and have a Hero Pass- we are no strangers to the mountain and were considering a change for our friends whom we enjoy treating to trips to the snow as we are locals.
After that conversation with reception and their haughty, snide remarks about cost, I'm glad to be taking our business elsewhere.
Come for the food, but stay anywhere else :S

name: Sharnam Chopra
review_text:
Have had a great dining experience at the restaurant though was treated in a rude and condescending way over the phone when booking accomodation. I'm a regular to Falls Creek and a local North East resident.

I'll recommend the restaurant for sure but custom set service for the apartments was not good.

review_text: Stayed with a bunch of friends in one of the apartments. So clean, tidy and organised. Very comfortable beds, it has everything you need. Also the restaurant downstairs is awesome. Steak was incredibly good. Just make sure to make reservations because it's always very busy.

name: David McGregor
review_text: Delicious 12inch sub breaky

name: Derek Whitten
review_text: Great food and drinks, and a friendly atmosphere. Grab a marshmallow and toast it in their open fire while you're there!

name: Yusuke Tamaki
review_text: Incredible to find such quality restaurant up in the snow. The food was amazing , great service by the friendly wait staff, nice cozy atmosphere, there really is nothing to fault. Will definitely be going back again next trip.

name: Martin lin
review_text:
I cancelled my reservation with ST Falls Hotel over TWO months ago and have been chasing my refund ever since. I have sent two emails, made two phone calls, and even visited the hotel in person last week, where the manager assured me the refund would be processed immediately.

It's now 60 days later and I STILL haven't received my money. No confirmation. No follow-up. Nothing. This is completely unacceptable and shows a total lack of professionalism and integrity.

Under Australian Consumer Law, I'm entitled to a prompt refund. The fact that I have to keep chasing you for what is legally mine is beyond frustrating. Your failure to act is not only a terrible customer service experience, it's a breach of consumer protection laws.

If you value your money and your time, do NOT book here. I will be reporting this to the ACCC and relevant authorities.

name: Priyal Rama Asary
review_text: Just had a really good stay after being upgraded to a 2 bedroom apartment (yay!). Staff were very helpful and the location makes life so easy for ski school dropoff. The hot tub was great after a day of skiing too.

name: WaiJane Lai
review_text:
We had a fantastic stay at St. Falls Resort, and a big part of that was thanks to Jerry from customer service. He was incredibly helpful, attentive, and truly dedicated to making sure our experience was smooth and enjoyable.

From the moment we arrived, Jerry went above and beyond to assist us always with a warm attitude and genuine care. It's rare to come across such professional and thoughtful service these days.

The resort itself is beautiful, but it's the top-notch service that really sets it apart.
Highly recommended, and a special shoutout to Jerry for making our stay so memorable.

name: F L
review_text: Terrible customer service. Staff are unhelpful and just push responsibility around. After cancelling my booking, I was only offered a vague credit with no clear rules. Absolutely no real support when you need it. Never coming back!

name: Chloe Hodgkinson
review_text: Don't waste your money. Was better options for places to stay! Not worth the $$ and staff were not helpful. Will not return!
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Chloe, thank you for your feedback. We're very sorry to hear about your disappointment upon check in and how this impacted the start of your holiday. 

We understand your frustration about the room view not meeting expectations, especially after you had taken the time to confirm this with us ahead of your arrival. Please know that we take these matters seriously and always aim to resolve concerns as soon as they are brought to our attention   

We also wanted to clarify that your email arrived just 15 minutes before this review was posted, which unfortunately did not allow us any reasonable opportunity to address your concerns or try to make things right before this became public. Had we been given that chance, we absolutely would have done everything possible to help. 

Regardless, we appreciate your feedback as it helps us improve, and we wish you the very best  for your future travels.

name: shayne svenson
review_text:
One of the worst dining experiences I've
hot chocolate, no milk, sugar or tea spoon. I had asked twice, once each for milk, then sugar, ended up using my fork to stir my tea, as asking a third time is B.S. IMO.

name: Jacqui Bullock
review_text: Do not stay here.  Soundproofing is appalling.  We have been kept awake multiple nights due to our neighbors in the floor below having a wow of a time  in the spa (which sits directly under the bedroom windows of our apartment).  We can hear every word they say (even at normal speaking voice).  Apparently reception can't do much about it because it's an owner.  But as a guest paying significant sums of money you can't make noise after 10pm.  You also can't even speak to anyone at reception after 11pm to try and problem solve the issue.

name: Ruby Chan
review_text:
3 star service apartment with 5 star price tag. Terrible sound proof, can hear our neighbours conversations all the time and the noise downstairs. Our one bedroom spa apartment view was facing the carpark which is very disappointing and I booked 9 months ago!
In terms of customer service, there was none. I asked them if they can please give me lift to spa up the road because I have an ACL knee injury from DAY 1 of my 7 days ski trip, I can see the hotel buggy just sitting at the front from my bedroom all day. They said its not for guests, only for the staff. I asked them I have been sitting in the apartment for the last 5 days just hoping to do something to make myself feel better but the response from them was cold , hard: 'no, sorry we cant help u.' This is not a 5 star hotel service for sure.

name: Adrian William Baulderstone
review_text: The rooms are comfortable, clean and tidy. The location is excellent and the service was great.

name: S R
review_text: At restaurant 1550 We waited for more than 30 mins for the food to come and then found a beetle falling out from my salads. The staff said they could refund the food and then took my food away. On checkout the staff said my food has been discounted so we paid the bill. After we arrived home, we realized they only discounted $5 for only 20% food I have consumed. Have written complaint email to them about my experience but never responded! Even no apologies. Very unpleasant experience about the waiting time, their overcharge and attitudes in regards to complaints. Never visit again!

name: D G
review_text: What a fantastic location. You couldn't go past this, right at the base of Halley's Comet which meant not having the wait forever for the village shuttle - which we did last year because we stayed further away and wasted so much time. It's next to falls creek sports and homebase to pick up all tickets and ski hire, and there's restaurents, cafes and a supermarket literally next door. The apartment was spotless. Had everything we needed including a fantastic drying cupboard and good heating. We used the pool and sauna which was lovely. The people working are also super nice and helpful and they allowed us to check in very early and also came without delay to help fix our tv. The restaurant 1550 was also very nice and the staff there so lovely. But without doubt it was the location that makes it worth every $$. Thanks again to everyone there. We will definitely be back next year without doubt!

name: Lorida J O'Shannessy
review_text:
Our issue was not with our stay but with the fact this accommodation and their staff lack a level of customer care. We had this accomm force a cancellation last minute as they tried to extort more money a couple of weeks before we were due to stay. We booked more than 3 months in advance for 6 people and were in constant contact right from the start and paid a substantially deposit. This place was a 2 bedroom apartment and we made it clear there were 4 adults plus 2 children.
They never mentioned any additional charges up front.
However, a couple of weeks out after the cancellation period had lapsed we had the accommodation contact us and tell us that we have to pay $75 for an extra "bed"
They continued to contact us and the story changed aswell as the price going up to $100 and then $150 for first the use of a futon couch and then a "per child" fee.
This place caused absolute undue stress and we had to find somewhere very last minute.
But the way they approached things lacked any customer service and seemed quite odd and off.
We actually reported these guys to consumer affairs and the ACCC.
Don't risk the stay here.

name: Andy Tamlin
review_text:
I'd like to start by saying we booked pretty late, and as a result paid probably a lot more than your average room. It was definitely on the expensive side, and for that price you would expect top quality in most if not all respects.
The apartment itself was fairly small. We had a 2 bedroom spa apartment, and it was just big enough for 4 people.
The room itself was wildly under equipped with basic cooking essentials. We mentioned this to the staff, and they did everything they could to find what we needed, big props. It turns out the rooms are privately owned, and so if the owners haven't equipped the rooms properly for cooking and cleaning, it's St Falls who end up looking bad. We really appreciate their assistance with everything trying to help out where possible.

Location, bang on. Literally doesn't get better.

Bedrooms and bathrooms were functional but not efficient. The exhaust fans in the bathrooms didn't do a whole lot, so foggy mirrors was a regular occurrence.

The sofa bed was also a bit rough to sleep on. We found that in order for it to be comfortable enough, using the doona under and over the top like a burrito worked the best for extra padding.

Heated floors throughout the apartment were fantastic. No issues at all.

A few things to note is that St Falls has only taken over from QT, so the resort is still needing a fair bit of work to get to what they are charging. Additionally the pool is not what we were expecting for a 5 star resort, more like a large kids pool.

All in all, we enjoyed our stay, and think that even with everything, the location made it worthwhile to stay here.

name: MicroO
review_text: Gym and pool included. Quite a lot of local restaurants and 30 second walk to the nearest chairlift. Rooms were lovely and spacious and service is great! Local supermarket right underneath the hotel, so super convenient!

name: Catherine Roosenburg
review_text:
Location was a 10/10 directly behind the main chairlift up to Cloud 9. Super easy to hire your gear from Base Camp in the same complex as well as super convenient drive in location.
Staff were all VERY friendly (Michelle) and everyone really helpful.
Restaurant 1550 simple but really delicious food we ate there twice and great coffee, again friendly staff (Amber)

Perhaps the only drawback given the price of what you are paying is the quality of the rooms. Slightly run down in need of some new blinds and furnishings and no cleaning service.

Management is new and they are doing their very best first season in.

Have booked for two trips next season already.

name: zoe rake
review_text: Best location to the main area and lift up the mountain, good amenities (heated pool and steam room) ski hire etc, food and beverage, parking etc. wouldn't stay elsewhere

name: Paul Licina
review_text:
So disappointing.
The place is rundown. I understand that management has recently changed but it is unfair to charge 5 star prices for a 2 star establishment. Checkin was delayed by over an hour beyond the already very late checkin time of 4pm because the couch was broken. No chance of getting into the room for a quick afternoon ski. Two days later on a rainy day while watching a movie we were all displaced by the delivery guys literally tearing the broken couch apart to get it out of the room and bringing a new one in. The room is tired. Paint peeling. Cheap furniture. No complete sets of any glassware or crockery. For $1800 a night our spa looked over the public car park so no view and no privacy but a great deal of noise despite a view being advertised. The location of the hotel is so convenient, but think twice before booking if you are accustomed to high quality accommodation.

name: Mohsin M
review_text:
Worst Restaurant on the Mountain. Should be the last place you would want to visit to eat.

If you want to experience the worst customer service and a group of really rude staff then this is your place.

name: Lola Smith
review_text: This place is amazing. Michelle and her team on the front desk are so friendly and helpful! This is what we love about Falls Creek and we will definitely keep coming back. Highly recommend!

name: Edwin Polis
review_text: My family and I decided to stay at Falls Creek during the Queens Birthday long weekend. I was really impressed by all the staff given their politness and willing to assist us on all our concerns. The rooms were small but modern and kept warm all day round. Thank you to the team.

name: Esin
review_text:
Lovely accommodation. clean, neat and comfortable.

Restaurant has great food too.

name: Mark Blakey
review_text: This hotel has been recently taken over, and having myself owned a venue during Covid-19 I was generally willing to give them the benefit of the doubt, as Kate (A very hard working manager) tries to get the team up to speed. You have to consider that this Hotel cost us $540 per night. I've stayed in some pretty fancy hotels around the world for less than that, so I have some small expectations of a hotel in this price bracket. However my patience ran out quickly. In what should have been our last evening of sitting on our balcony enjoying the view. We could NOT sit outside as several members of STAFF were below our balcony SMOKING (for 3 hours) in a hotel? In 2021? Bizarre!! Further to this the STAFF conversation was mainly centred around which customers had been a pain during...

name: Sam Sung
review_text: Great spa, stunning view dow the Kiewa Valley.

name: Brett Middleton
review_text: Really impressed with the skidoo tours. Such a wonderful way to see the resort. Bruce and co were really helpful in explaining the scenery.

name: Chloe Zilin Zhou
review_text:
Great place to learn how to ski with lots of tracks for all levels 

Best time to visit is during June-August as there is more snow that time. You can also rent lodges in front of the ski lift for convenience but keep in mind they are around $1200 per night. 

The staff are really nice and always strike up conversations with you on the mouse trap like "how's your day going?" or "Give me a fist bump man!" 

The weather is really cold and I ended up not wearing my goggles because it was really snowy and foggy in that day. 

I was a beginner and had just started skiing with no experience and I learnt quickly and went on to ski the blue and green tracks on my second day so I do recommend taking classes.  There are adult and child classes depending on your level.

Definitely recommend Falls Creek! Staff are nice and lifts and transport are nice and well kept too!  Will definitely come back next year!

name: Arienn Eiranwen
review_text:
Disrespectful Pricing, No Support -- We're Going Elsewhere

Spent over $2,400 for just 3 days of skiing with the kids -- and on top of that, they charge you just to get the card for the lift pass. Had a genuine medical reason (broken toe) and tried to request the early bird discount after missing the deadline, but no response for over 3 weeks. No phone number. Just emails into a black hole.

Customer service is non-existent, pricing is predatory, and there's zero compassion or flexibility. Everything is overpriced -- rentals, tickets, even kids' lessons. The system is built to extract every dollar while offering the bare minimum in return.

We'll be taking our family to a snowfield that values its visitors and treats them like human beings next time-- Falls Creek is not it.

name: Sam Baker
review_text: Good skiing

name: Sam Brun
review_text: Great place, it misses on a star for the price as a lift ticket for 1 day is around $170. Definitely get the cheap passes if you are staying longer but otherwise just as expected, great lifts and good runs would come back

name: Samantha Smith
review_text: I recently spent a week here with my husband and 2 teenage children. We had a ball! Great atmosphere, great places to stay and eat and staff were super friendly. Great resort for intermediate skiers.

name: Vincent Choi
review_text: One of the best ski field in Australia. The Snow is very good and it kicks start a very good season of 2023.

name: Ilana Steenkamp
review_text: This is a beautiful Ski resort with a stunning lake for fishing. It is also beautiful for hiking in the summer and mountain biking. The shops and restaurants were closed when we went there to have a quick look at the resort and wanted to grab something to eat. So just check restaurant opening times. But definitely worth a visit.

review_text: Nice tracks for all levels. Better choice for learning snowboard

name: C
review_text: Hugh ski resort both entry and intermediate level friendly. Was too busy playing ski and realised that I didn't have a lot of pictures. A little bit longer drive from Melbourne but you can park so much easier than Mt Buller.

name: Ron L
review_text: a last section of night run was completely blackout (no light pole), other than that was pretty good.

name: Amanda
review_text: Beautiful place great for skiing staff a little rude and abrupt would come back simply for the skiing. Better probably in July and August

name: Adrian Beer
review_text: Any day on the snow is great. Bluebird day's count extra, heli transport wins for sure. Awesome trip

name: P G
review_text: Covid aside I've been to Falls Creek most years since 1996 to ski. If you can afford it and you know what to expect (see other reviews for skiing) then fine. The key item is afford. You can't look out the window, see sunshine and think, today I will buy a lift ticket, unless you want to shell out 200 dollars per adult. tickets can be had cheaper if you book say two weeks in advance, but if the weather is dire and you don't want to ski on the day, money is lost. Yes you can cancel but by my understanding you loose 20 percent and the rest goes to a voucher that has to be used up in that season. On top of that the accommodation prices have rocketed since prior to Covid, it was always expensive but this is now "out of reach" expensive. On mountain facilities are of course captive audience excessive prices like concerts and sports events. So after all these years of being a loyal Falls Creek skier , I am now going to save up and ski somewhere where I don't feel I am being gouged and where the terrain, snow, food, facilities and weather , are significantly superior, e.g Japan

review_text:
Don't bother going to the zoo, as they have a couple of baboons operating the tow rope (lift) at the bottom of Falls Creek. At approximately 11am on the 29th of July 22, a young girl and old man were rude towards me when I was trying to learn the tow rope for the first time.

WON'T BE COMING BACK HERE

name: Geoff Woodcock
review_text: Been going here for the last 25 years but I've noticed with Vail taking over the admin and the running of the mountain overall seems to have deteriorated. Not as much in summer but winter. Mountain staff not as attentive as they should, grooming of slopes not up to scratch. It seems a lot of the attention to the smaller details that are lacking.
